@startuml 02-content-filter-engine
!theme plain
title In-page filter runtime (injected JS, per page load)

participant "Instagram router\n(history.pushState/\nreplaceState, patched)" as History
participant "MutationObserver" as Observer
participant "scan()" as Scan
participant "DOM" as DOM

== Document start (before first paint) ==
Scan -> DOM : injectStyle()\nappend <style id="sg-style"> once
Scan -> DOM : updateRoute()\nhtml[data-sg-path] = location.pathname
Scan -> DOM : unhideStaleUnits()\nre-check existing [data-sg-hidden] nodes
Scan -> DOM : hideSuggestedUnits()\nTreeWalker scans text nodes for marker labels

note right of Scan
  A marker match climbs the DOM to the
  nearest <article>, or the outermost
  ancestor with no real post inside
  (hop-capped, stops at main/body).
end note

== SPA navigation (no full page load) ==
DOM -> History : pushState(...) (user taps a tab)
History -> Scan : onNavigate()
Scan -> Scan : enforceRoutes()\ndoes pathname start with a blocked prefix?
alt blocked route (e.g. /reels)
    Scan -> DOM : location.replace('/')
else allowed route
    Scan -> DOM : updateRoute()
    Scan -> Scan : scheduleScan()\n(200ms debounce)
end

== Lazy-rendered feed content ==
DOM -> Observer : childList mutation\n(React renders more posts)
Observer -> Scan : scheduleScan()
Scan -> DOM : unhideStaleUnits()
note right of DOM
  React can recycle a hidden node for a
  real post; unhide anything that no
  longer contains a marker text node.
end note
Scan -> DOM : hideSuggestedUnits()
@enduml
